Kenya Power customers will not be able to make online payments for their postpaid bills tomorrow Saturday from 4 pm to Sunday at 6 am. This, according to the company is to enable system maintenance to enhance efficiency. However, no customer will be disconnected for failure to pay their bill during this time. The exercise will not affect token purchase under the prepaid vending system. Last month, Kenyans expressed their frustration over the delays in getting prepaid tokens from the Kenya Power and Lighting Company. Some of the customers questioned why the company took so long to address the issue. Read More: KOT angered by Kenya Power's prepaid token delays  